===Article===
'''the''' 

# Definite [[w:grammatical article|grammatical article]] in [[w:English language|English]].  Unlike many languages, English does not inflect its articles for gender, case or number.
#: ''The word ''the'' is the most common word in the English Language.''
#: ''The men, the women, the boy and the girl watched the birds eat the birdseed.''
# When stressed, indicates that the object in question is the best or the only one worthy of attention.
#: ''That is ''the'' hospital to go to for heart surgery.''
# With an adjective, indicates all persons to whom the adjective applies.
#: ''Feed the hungry, clothe the naked, comfort the afflicted, and afflict the comfortable.''
# With a [[comparative]] or ''[[more]]'' and a verb phrase, establishes a parallel with another comparison (often but not always a similar construction with ''the'').
#: ''The more I think about it, the weaker it looks.''
#: ''The hotter the better.''
#: ''It looks weaker and weaker, the more I think about it.''
# With a [[superlative]], indicates the person or thing to which the superlative applies.
#: ''That apple pie was the best.''

