===Pronunciation===
*(''unstressed''): <i>th</i>ə, /ðə/, /D@/
*(''stressed''): <i>th</i>ē, /ðiː/, /Di:/

''The'' is generally unstressed, except as noted above or in reference.  E.g., in "The word ''the''", the second instance is stressed.

<!-- The exact handling of ''the'' before vowels has to do with the phonology of the dialect in question.  The rule originally given (long e before vowels) is by no means universal -->

===Etymology===

Old English ''&thorn;&aelig;t'', neuter article; Middle English ''&thorn;&aelig;t'', definite article.

